						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab standing in front of the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Vikramāditya VI]—A.D. 1086.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 10, Krōdhana, Phālguṇa, śu. 1, Sunday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1086, February 17,</hi> the weekday being <hi rend="bold">Tuesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of 100 <hi rend="italic">mattars</hi> of land at <hi rend="bold">Eḷamēla</hi> by Manḍalika <hi rend="bold">Nāyimarasa.</hi> The record falls in the reign-period of Vikramāditya VI. </p>						

						</summary>
